sentences: Crystal Caines is a Guyanese–American rapper, hip hop record producer, artist, songwriter and engineer based in Harlem, New York.
She began her production career in 2012.

In 2013, Caines produced the Bone Thugs-n-Harmony-featuring "Lord" on A$AP Ferg's debut album, Trap Lord, Continuing on to also engineering and premixing vocals for A$AP Ferg's future singles, "Work", "Shabba” and majority of the TrapLord Album.
In 2014, she released her debut single and Video, "Whiteline".
